{"id":721677811,"lang":"python3","time":"3 weeks, 2 days","timestamp":1655172140,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"352 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/721677811/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Delete Operation for Two Strings","memory":"16.1 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def minDistance(self, word1: str, word2: str) -> int:\n        n1 = len(word1)\n        n2 = len(word2)\n        f = [[0 for _ in range(n2 + 1)] for _ in range(n1 + 1)]\n        for i in range(1, n1 + 1):\n            for j in range(1, n2 + 1):\n                if word1[i - 1] == word2[j - 1]:\n                    f[i][j] = f[i - 1][j - 1] + 1\n                else:\n                    f[i][j] = max(f[i - 1][j], f[i][j - 1])\n        res = n1 + n2 - 2 * f[n1][n2]\n        return res","compare_result":"","title_slug":"delete-operation-for-two-strings"}
